  <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

  <p>
    At <strong>9jastay</strong>, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your
    personal information is handled in a safe and responsible manner. This Privacy Policy
    explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use
    our website, mobile applications, and related services.
  </p>

  <p>
    By accessing or using the 9jastay platform, you agree to the collection and use of
    information in accordance with this policy.
  </p>

  <h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>

  <p>We may collect different types of information in order to provide and improve our services:</p>

  <h5>Personal Information</h5>
  <p>
    When you create an account, make a booking, list a property, or contact our support team,
    we may collect personal details such as:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Full name</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Phone number</li>
    <li>Account login credentials</li>
    <li>Profile information</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Booking and Transaction Information</h5>
  <p>
    When you book a property or list accommodation on 9jastay, we may collect information
    related to the booking or transaction including:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Property details</li>
    <li>Booking dates and duration</li>
    <li>Payment details and transaction history</li>
    <li>Communication between guests and vendors</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Device and Usage Information</h5>
  <p>
    We may automatically collect information about the device and how our services are used,
    including:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>IP address</li>
    <li>Device type and operating system</li>
    <li>Browser type</li>
    <li>Pages visited and features used</li>
    <li>Location data (if enabled)</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>

  <p>The information we collect helps us operate and improve our services. We may use your information to:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Facilitate property bookings and reservations</li>
    <li>Connect guests with property owners and vendors</li>
    <li>Process secure payments and transactions</li>
    <li>Provide customer support and respond to inquiries</li>
    <li>Improve our website, applications, and services</li>
    <li>Send important service notifications or updates</li>
    <li>Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, or illegal activity</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>3. Sharing of Information</h4>

  <p>
    We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may
    share your information in certain circumstances, including:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>With property owners or vendors when you make a booking</li>
    <li>With trusted service providers who assist in operating the platform</li>
    <li>With payment processors to complete transactions</li>
    <li>When required by law, legal process, or government authorities</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>4. Data Security</h4>

  <p>
    We implement appropriate administrative, technical, and physical security measures
    designed to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure,
    alteration, or destruction.
  </p>

  <p>
    While we strive to protect your data, no system can guarantee absolute security.
    Users are encouraged to keep their login credentials confidential.
  </p>

  <h4>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h4>

  <p>
    Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience,
    remember your preferences, analyze traffic, and improve the performance of our platform.
  </p>

  <p>
    You may adjust your browser settings to refuse cookies; however, some features of the
    platform may not function properly.
  </p>

  <h4>6. Third-Party Services</h4>

  <p>
    9jastay may integrate with third-party services such as payment gateways, analytics
    providers, or authentication services. These third parties may collect and process
    certain data in accordance with their own privacy policies.
  </p>

  <h4>7. User Rights and Choices</h4>

  <p>
    You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information. You may also
    request that we limit the processing of your data or opt out of certain communications.
  </p>

  <p>
    To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.
  </p>

  <h4>8. Children's Privacy</h4>

  <p>
    Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly
    collect personal information from children. If we become aware that a child has provided
    personal information, we will take steps to remove such data.
  </p>

  <h4>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h4>

  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices,
    technology, legal requirements, or platform features. When we update this policy, we
    will revise the "Last Updated" date and notify users when appropriate.
  </p>

  <h4>10. Contact Us</h4>

  <p>
    If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how your information
    is handled, please contact us at:
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong> support@9jastay.com<br>
    <strong>Website:</strong> www.9jastay.com
  </p>

  <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2026</p>

